OL,3,CRecycling firm fined #2m after worker
OL,4,Chit and crushed by shovel loader
OL,6,FWard Recycling, which was based on
OL,7,FHartlepool's Longhill Industrial
OL,8,FEstate, but has since gone into
OL,9,Fadministration, was found guilty of
OL,10,Fcorporate manslaughter and health and
OL,11,Fsafety breaches, after a trial at
OL,12,FTeesside Crown Court in December.
OL,14,FThe company has been fined #2.15m for
OL,15,Fwhat the judge called "truly
OL,16,Fstaggering health and safety failures"
OL,17,Fat the plant, which had no traffic
OL,18,Fmanagement plan to ensure workers
OL,19,Fcould safely walk across the plant's
OL,20,Ffloor to the staff toilets, which were
OL,21,Fin an outside building.
