OL,3,CRecycling firm fined #2m after worker
OL,4,Chit and crushed by shovel loader
OL,6,FThe court heard he was wearing a
OL,7,F"bright orange high visibility jacket
OL,8,Fand trousers" when he crossed the
OL,9,Ffloor. At 8.37am on 30 January 2020,
OL,10,Fhe was struck in the head by the
OL,11,Fshovel loader and crushed under its
OL,12,Fwheels, killing him instantly.
OL,14,FAnother employee shouted at the driver
OL,15,Fto stop, but the driver could not hear
OL,16,Fhim over the noise of the engine and
OL,17,Fthe operating machinery. The police
OL,18,Fand the Health and Safety Executive
OL,19,F(HSE) began an investigation that day.
