OL,3,CRecycling firm fined #2m after worker
OL,4,Chit and crushed by shovel loader
OL,6,FAllan Compton, prosecuting, told the
OL,7,Fcourt: "Lots of vehicles were moving
OL,8,Faround, and people - who walked to the
OL,9,Ffacilities - had to cross the main
OL,10,Ffloor of the building where the plant
OL,11,Fmachines were operating. Visibility,
OL,12,Ffor the vehicle driver, was restricted
OL,13,Fand the driver did not see Mr Atkinson.
OL,15,F"There was a failure to have any
OL,16,Ftraffic management in place,
OL,17,Fseparating traffic and pedestrians.
OL,18,FThere was a failure to provide
OL,19,Fadequate instructions to employees
OL,20,Fwhen walking or driving in the
OL,21,Fbuilding."
